<slide><h2>The Rise of XML</h2>
<!-- === rewrite === -->
<p> Perhaps the one area of convergence:
</p>
<ul>
  <li> XML is a standardized syntax
  </li>
  <li> ... with no associated semantics
  </li>
  <li> Good for:
       <ul>
	 <li> text with markup
	 </li>
	 <li> data
	 </li>
       </ul>
  </li>
  <li> Easy for computers to read and write
  </li>
  <li> not so easy for humans,
  </li>
  <li> ... but the tools are getting better
  </li>
</ul>
</slide>

