<set name="subcaption">Challenges for Web Application Developers</set>
<slide><h2>Challenges for Web Application Developers</h2>
<p> &nbsp;</p>
<ul>
  <li> Which platform?
  </li>
  <li> How to collaborate?
  </li>
  <li> Which development environment?
  </li>
  <li> How to maintain / customize?
  </li>
</ul>
</slide>

<slide><h2>Which platform?</h2>
<p align="center"> <strong>platform = ( server, OS, language )</strong> 
<br />
    <img src="Images/widening.png" />
</p>
</slide>

<slide><h2>How to Collaborate?</h2>
<ul>
  <li> Many people work on a web application
       <ul>
	 <li> ...over time
	 </li>
	 <li> ...at the same time
	 </li>
       </ul>
  </li>
  <li> Some have specialized skills
       <ul>
	 <li> writers
	 </li>
	 <li> artists
	 </li>
	 <li> application designers
	 </li>
	 <li> web designers
	 </li>
	 <li> program designers
	 </li>
       </ul>
  </li>
</ul>
</slide>

<slide><h2>Which Development Environment?</h2>
<ul>
  <li> From ``notepad'' and <code>emacs</code>
  </li>
  <li> ... to integrated HTML editors
  </li>
  <li> ... ... to publishing frameworks
  </li>
       <p> 
       </p>
  <li> Different developers have different preferences
  </li>
  <li> Tools should not interfere with one another
  </li>
</ul>
</slide>

<slide><h2>How to Maintain and Customize?</h2>
<ul>
  <li> Customization and maintenance are closely related
       <ul>
	 <li> an application that is easy to customize
	 </li>
	 <li> ... is also easy to maintain
	 </li>
       </ul>
  </li>
  <li> Customizing and interacting users may have simpler needs<br />
       ... or they may be computer experts themselves.
  </li>
  <li> Documents are easy to maintain<br />
       ... programs are hard
  </li>
</ul>
</slide>

<hide>
<!-- === old === -->
<slide><h2>Requirements for Web Applications</h2>
<ul>
  <li> Cross Platform 
  </li>
  <li> Client Neutral
  </li>
  <li> Scalable
  </li>
  <li> Stable Interfaces
       <ul>
	 <li> interfaces must not change if implementation changes.
	 </li>
       </ul>
  </li>
  <li> Customizable
  </li>
</ul>
</slide>

<slide><h2>Requirements for Application Development</h2>
<ul>
  <li> Support wide range of skill levels
       <ul>
	 <li> allow customization by non-experts
	 </li>
       </ul>
  </li>
  <li> Strong support for markup languages (XML, HTML)
  </li>
  <li> Support for distributed development
  </li>
  <li> Platform neutral
  </li>
  <li> Tool neutral
       <ul>
	 <li> support for adding new tools
	 </li>
	 <li> tools should preserve source-level formatting
	 </li>
       </ul>
  </li>
</ul>
</slide>
</hide>

<set name="subcaption">The PIA Solution: XML-based  framework</set>
<slide><h2>The PIA Solution</h2>

<p align="center"> <strong>An XML-based framework for web applications</strong>
</p>

<ul>
  <li> uses a single XML-based language for :
       <ul>
	 <li> document markup (content)
	 </li>
	 <li> data
	 </li>
	 <li> behavior
	 </li>
       </ul>
  </li>
  <li> Small, simple document-processing engine
       <ul>
	 <li> easily integrated into many platforms
	 </li>
       </ul>
  </li>
  <li> Versatile site-description package
  </li>
  <li> Applications consist entirely of XML documents
       <ul>
	 <li> maintain and develop with standard tools
	 </li>
	 <li> easily customized
	 </li>
	 <li> friendly to text-based version control systems
	 </li>
       </ul>
  </li>
  <li> Open source at <a href="http://RiSource.org/"><font face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif" color="#993300">Ri</font><font face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif" color="black"><i>Source.org</i></font></a>
  </li>
</ul>
